\backslash
subsection*{Mirrors:
 The New Reflection}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Scala 3 introduces 
\backslash
texttt{Mirror}.
 A Mirror is a compile-time representation of a class's shape.
 It tells you the names of the fields and their types without ever needing to "instantiate" the class.
 This is how libraries like 
\backslash
texttt{Doobie} map database rows to your Case Classes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{verbatim}
\end_layout

